Time for another Filipino hidden gem.
Itâ€™s been a while since I checked out a new Filipino restaurant so today Iâ€™m here at Pinoy Corner Restaurant ordering three very traditional Filipino dishes.
Number one is a big seafood platter. This one is good for 3 to 4 people and it comes with shrimp, mussels, squid, crab, lobster, corn, salted egg, so delicious and all of it is on rice.
I also ordered Bulalo which is a traditional Filipino beef stew. It comes with bone marrow and corn and some greens in a clear broth.

And not to miss the famous Chicken Adobo, which is chicken with a sauce made of vinegar and soy sauce. I had this dish before a long time ago and I still love it. I heard they call it the national dish of the Philippines, so this is a must try when you come to a Filipino restaurant.
Let me know in the comments which Filipino dish is your favorite!
